# Global QA Rules

- Never start a full QA execution session without both requirements and app URL.
- Always load knowledge base before requirements analysis, test generation, or test review.
- Always check known defects before filing bugs.
- Always capture artifacts for failures during execution.
- Always link Jira bugs back to Qase when possible.
- Always save screenshots and logs under `qa-artifacts/`.
- Always use safe placeholder test data.
- Never use real passwords, tokens, cookies, API keys, or production PII.
- Never invent test results, Jira keys, Qase IDs, or artifact paths.
- Never claim external system updates unless confirmed.
- Never file duplicate bugs when known defect exists.
- Never classify unclear behavior as confirmed defect without a requirement or strong evidence.
- Never put test data in preconditions when writing/reviewing test cases.
- Always separate product defect, test case defect, environment issue, and requirement ambiguity.
- Always include positive, negative, edge, security, permission, API, DB, and regression coverage when applicable.
- Always include pagination/search/filter/sort coverage for list screens.
- Always include CRUD coverage for menu modules that support register, edit, delete, and search.
- Always include Qase/Jira-friendly summaries when those tools are in scope.
- Always provide a local artifact when a workflow produces substantial output.

